  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Stephen Hawking
Lived:         1942 - 2018
Nationality:   English
Field:         Physics
Known For:     Black hole radiation
Contribution:  Proved black holes emit radiation; A Brief History of Time; communicated science publicly
Quote:         "Intelligence is the ability to adapt to change."

Name:          Tim Berners-Lee
Lived:         1955 - present
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     World Wide Web
Contribution:  Invented the Web in 1989; gave it to the world for free
Quote:         "The web does not just connect machines, it connects people."

Name:          Florence Nightingale
Lived:         1820 - 1910
Nationality:   English
Field:         Medicine
Known For:     Modern nursing
Contribution:  Founded modern nursing; used statistics; reduced Crimean War mortality 40% to 2%
Quote:         "I attribute my success to this: I never gave or took any excuse."

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Fundamental Theorem of Calculus
Branch:       Calculus
Formula:      ∫[a,b] f'(x)dx = f(b) - f(a)
Applications: Physics, engineering, economics
Discoverer:   Newton/Leibniz (1670)

Theorem/Law:  Bayes Theorem
Branch:       Probability
Formula:      P(H|E) = P(E|H)P(H)/P(E)
Applications: ML, spam filters, medical testing
Discoverer:   Thomas Bayes (1763)

Theorem/Law:  Taylor Series
Branch:       Calculus
Formula:      f(x) = sum of f^n(a)/n! * (x-a)^n
Applications: Numerical computation, signal processing
Discoverer:   Brook Taylor (1715)

